The paper deals with the problem of facial action unit detection using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also explores different design choices for the CNN architecture, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The use of motion information in addition to color information suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the efficiency and modularity of the proposed approach, which could be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of an ensemble of action unit detectors suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
